WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:23.880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:29.260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:37.010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:43.120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

00:00:44.650 --> 00:00:47.930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:51.000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:56.660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:00.880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:04.160
♪The open sky rises high♪

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:09.830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:17.220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:23.300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

00:01:23.710 --> 00:01:26.960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:30.290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:34.730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:35.980
=The Lead=

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.980
=Episode 3=

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:39.420
Director Huang, what do you think?

00:01:40.380 --> 00:01:41.580
Even Mi Lan can go.

00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:43.900
How about letting me play
for the officials?

00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:45.020
As for creative matters,

00:01:45.580 --> 00:01:46.940
Deputy Director Zhu makes the call.

00:01:47.540 --> 00:01:48.380
Director Zhu,

00:01:48.460 --> 00:01:49.420
what do you think?

00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:53.060
Hu Sanyuan is the band's team leader.

00:01:53.060 --> 00:01:54.660
Band matters are up to him.

00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:56.060
Up to him?

00:01:56.060 --> 00:01:57.500
That guy would let me play?

00:01:57.500 --> 00:01:59.140
How am I worse than him at it?

00:01:59.140 --> 00:02:00.220
Exactly how am I worse?

00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:02.020
He Dachui's drumming is a mess.

00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:04.340
If he plays drums, I can't sing.

00:02:04.340 --> 00:02:05.260
Mi Lan,

00:02:05.740 --> 00:02:07.020
listen to yourself.

00:02:08.140 --> 00:02:10.460
Acting high and mighty before the show.

00:02:10.460 --> 00:02:12.060
Don't pin the blame on me.

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:12.980
You just can't sing.

00:02:12.980 --> 00:02:14.340
Why blame the drums?

00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:15.780
I'm done helping.

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:16.620
I'm leaving.

00:02:17.260 --> 00:02:18.100
He Dachui.

00:02:18.740 --> 00:02:19.580
What is it?

00:02:20.260 --> 00:02:21.300
You trying to quit on us?

00:02:21.300 --> 00:02:22.300
Who said I was quitting?

00:02:22.300 --> 00:02:23.340
They won't let me play.

00:02:23.340 --> 00:02:24.180
Go sit back down.

00:02:26.860 --> 00:02:28.260
Alright, let's rehearse.

00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:29.100
Director Huang,

00:02:29.780 --> 00:02:30.900
for no reason at all,

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:32.820
your family caused a huge scene here.

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:34.500
The examiners have left.

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:35.860
Now, we can't even perform.

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:38.940
I figure if I didn't make a move on you,

00:02:39.900 --> 00:02:40.980
I'd be taking the blame for nothing.

00:02:40.980 --> 00:02:42.260
What are you saying?

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:44.420
What do you want?

00:02:45.420 --> 00:02:47.060
I wanted to have a heart-to-heart.

00:02:49.340 --> 00:02:51.860
I'm just trying to better myself.

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:52.700
Don't come over here.

00:02:52.700 --> 00:02:54.660
I wanted a deeper talk with you.

00:02:55.940 --> 00:02:57.420
Just a deeper talk.

00:02:58.100 --> 00:02:58.940
About self-improvement.

00:02:58.940 --> 00:03:00.020
Why are you hiding?

00:03:00.020 --> 00:03:01.940
Come on, let's talk it through.

00:03:03.380 --> 00:03:04.540
Talk! Talk!

00:03:04.900 --> 00:03:05.740
Stay right there.

00:03:05.740 --> 00:03:06.860
Let's talk it through.

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:08.740
Just exchanging thoughts. Come on.

00:03:08.740 --> 00:03:09.580
Don't come closer.

00:03:09.580 --> 00:03:10.860
Why are you dodging me?

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:12.100
- Don't you like it?
- Be decent.

00:03:12.100 --> 00:03:12.940
- Huang Zhengjing.
- Talk.

00:03:13.580 --> 00:03:14.500
What are you two doing?

00:03:23.580 --> 00:03:24.500
This is bad now.

00:03:57.380 --> 00:03:58.380
Why are you following me?

00:03:59.740 --> 00:04:01.780
Like medicated plaster,
you were stuck on me.

00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:21.820
I don't even want

00:04:22.260 --> 00:04:23.300
to sing in that show.

00:04:34.340 --> 00:04:35.940
So, how's it going? Did she sing?

00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:40.500
What's gotten into you?

00:04:41.060 --> 00:04:41.940
Didn't we agree on this?

00:04:41.940 --> 00:04:43.540
Why are you backing out again?

00:04:43.540 --> 00:04:44.700
This has nothing to do with the kid.

00:04:45.260 --> 00:04:46.100
I'm not in the mood.

00:04:47.740 --> 00:04:48.860
We need to hurry.

00:04:48.860 --> 00:04:50.300
The audition is in two days.

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:51.460
No matter how she sings,

00:04:51.460 --> 00:04:52.580
we've got to get her to start.

00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:02.460
Why are you sulking right now?

00:05:03.380 --> 00:05:05.740
You've done that tired old show enough.

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:06.900
Why do it again?

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:08.580
Let her do it.

00:05:10.140 --> 00:05:12.180
Save your voice for the new show.

00:05:14.980 --> 00:05:17.140
She's nowhere near as good as you.

00:05:21.500 --> 00:05:22.340
Just you wait.

00:05:22.340 --> 00:05:24.380
Tonight, I'll pound the drum to pieces.

00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:26.500
She'll sing, huh?

00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:28.820
What did you say?

00:05:29.500 --> 00:05:31.540
She's nowhere near as good as you.

00:05:34.820 --> 00:05:37.020
Tonight, I'll pound the drum to pieces.

00:05:37.380 --> 00:05:38.500
Your words, not mine.

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:48.220
Why did I say that?

00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:57.780
When women clash, it gets ugly.

00:05:58.580 --> 00:05:59.900
You'd better watch yourself later.

00:06:01.660 --> 00:06:02.900
We won't bother anyone.

00:06:05.260 --> 00:06:06.500
Come on, hold it up.

00:06:06.500 --> 00:06:07.380
Let's hurry up.

00:06:07.380 --> 00:06:08.220
Come on.

00:06:11.700 --> 00:06:14.060
Today, I'll take you in
from the front door.

00:06:14.060 --> 00:06:16.460
Let's see who the lead is.

00:06:18.020 --> 00:06:19.380
Tonight, we're in for a good show.

00:06:19.380 --> 00:06:21.820
We'll see your uncle smash that drum up.

00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:23.820
She'll blow the whole act.

00:06:24.700 --> 00:06:26.380
I do want to know how

00:06:26.380 --> 00:06:27.940
Huang Zhengjing will clean this up.

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:33.620
Why are you two arguing again?

00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:34.460
No way.

00:06:34.460 --> 00:06:35.660
I didn't see it, okay?

00:06:35.660 --> 00:06:36.740
You're playing dirty.

00:06:36.740 --> 00:06:38.660
You two fight here every day.

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:39.700
You always take back your move.

00:06:39.700 --> 00:06:40.860
And you've never done that?

00:06:40.860 --> 00:06:42.060
- Of course not.
- See?

00:06:42.260 --> 00:06:43.780
Learn anything but Xiangqi.

00:06:43.780 --> 00:06:45.340
It doesn't suit the lead's dignity.

00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:56.260
Hua Caixiang!

00:07:04.340 --> 00:07:05.900
(Today's show: Xiang Yang Hong)

00:07:15.020 --> 00:07:17.060
(Welcome the officials to our troupe)

00:07:28.900 --> 00:07:30.540
Isn't she just here to perform in opera?

00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:31.740
Do you really need all this?

00:07:31.740 --> 00:07:33.420
You dummy.

00:07:33.900 --> 00:07:36.140
Come on, I'll show you backstage.

00:07:37.780 --> 00:07:40.020
Over here is the offstage exit.

00:07:40.020 --> 00:07:42.020
The third wing curtain,
civil orchestra section.

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:43.300
They sit right up front.

00:07:45.260 --> 00:07:46.660
This is where we do makeup.

00:07:46.660 --> 00:07:48.100
- Ms. Hua.
- All dressed up already.

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:49.940
Ms. Hua.

00:07:49.940 --> 00:07:50.820
You're here.

00:07:50.820 --> 00:07:51.660
Ms. Hua.

00:07:52.420 --> 00:07:53.260
This is Aunt Bai.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:55.660
She handles costumes.

00:07:55.660 --> 00:07:57.380
These are the costumes we hang here.

00:07:59.740 --> 00:08:00.900
And these are the props.

00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:03.700
Why are you two dressed like this today?

00:08:04.180 --> 00:08:05.340
Look. Doesn't it look good?

00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:06.180
Gorgeous.

00:08:06.580 --> 00:08:08.060
Aunt Plump, Master Song.

00:08:08.060 --> 00:08:08.900
They run the kitchen.

00:08:11.780 --> 00:08:13.020
This is the onstage entrance.

00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:14.940
- The martial section is here.
- Who's that kid?

00:08:14.940 --> 00:08:15.860
Hu Sanyuan's niece.

00:08:15.860 --> 00:08:17.180
She's here to try for our trainee class.

00:08:18.860 --> 00:08:19.700
See that?

00:08:20.820 --> 00:08:23.300
Come on, everyone, put your work down.

00:08:23.300 --> 00:08:24.460
Director Huang has something to say.

00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:27.060
Gather in a little closer.

00:08:27.580 --> 00:08:28.460
Come on, come on.

00:08:32.820 --> 00:08:33.660
Comrades,

00:08:34.580 --> 00:08:36.420
I just got word.

00:08:36.420 --> 00:08:38.900
Tonight's guests are all officials
from the provincial capital.

00:08:39.780 --> 00:08:41.220
Everyone, stay sharp.

00:08:41.660 --> 00:08:43.700
This performance is a political task.

00:08:44.140 --> 00:08:46.060
No mistakes are allowed.

00:08:47.180 --> 00:08:48.020
Got it?

00:08:48.020 --> 00:08:49.100
Got it.

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:49.940
Applause.

00:08:54.940 --> 00:08:55.780
Good.

00:08:56.740 --> 00:08:57.580
Go and get ready.

00:08:57.580 --> 00:08:58.420
- Okay.
- Okay.

00:08:58.980 --> 00:08:59.820
Move it.

00:09:10.020 --> 00:09:11.580
Tonight depends on you.

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:18.340
Don't be nervous.

00:09:22.220 --> 00:09:24.260
Stop chatting and hurry up.

00:09:28.140 --> 00:09:30.380
The County Revolutionary Committee

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:32.740
said the official coming tonight
loves Qinqiang Opera.

00:09:33.580 --> 00:09:34.860
Can Mi Lan handle this?

00:09:35.540 --> 00:09:36.940
Should we switch back to Hua Caixiang?

00:09:37.340 --> 00:09:38.780
It's too late to swap her out now.

00:09:42.220 --> 00:09:44.180
(Welcome the officials here
for guidance)

00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:48.820
Who saw my plank?

00:09:49.660 --> 00:09:50.660
Has anyone seen my plank?

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:51.740
Move, move.

00:09:51.740 --> 00:09:52.660
What plank?

00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:53.580
My Xiyang.

00:09:53.580 --> 00:09:54.900
What's Xiyang?

00:09:55.500 --> 00:09:57.580
- Move.
- Keep it down. We're on standby.

00:09:57.580 --> 00:09:58.820
The audience is in. Keep it down.

00:09:58.820 --> 00:09:59.940
Has anyone seen my Xiyang?

00:10:00.300 --> 00:10:01.700
What's Xiyang?

00:10:02.020 --> 00:10:02.860
Have you seen my Xiyang?

00:10:02.980 --> 00:10:03.820
What Xiyang?

00:10:03.820 --> 00:10:04.660
What plank?

00:10:07.460 --> 00:10:08.700
Who saw my Xiyang?

00:10:08.700 --> 00:10:09.540
How many teeth?

00:10:09.980 --> 00:10:10.820
Quick, quick.

00:10:10.820 --> 00:10:11.660
What are you doing?

00:10:11.980 --> 00:10:12.860
Have you seen my Xiyang?

00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:13.780
- What?
- What Xiyang?

00:10:13.780 --> 00:10:14.620
The plank.

00:10:14.620 --> 00:10:15.860
Why are you in such a panic?

00:10:15.980 --> 00:10:16.980
My plank is gone.

00:10:22.420 --> 00:10:24.140
Why are you freaking out like this?

00:10:24.140 --> 00:10:25.060
What plank is missing?

00:10:25.860 --> 00:10:26.740
The scenery plank.

00:10:26.740 --> 00:10:27.740
The one with the character Xi.

00:10:28.380 --> 00:10:29.260
Where did you put it?

00:10:29.260 --> 00:10:30.100
I put it in the shed

00:10:30.100 --> 00:10:31.780
by the set storage room.

00:10:34.220 --> 00:10:35.540
How could you put it there?

00:10:35.940 --> 00:10:37.020
I thought it was useless,

00:10:37.020 --> 00:10:38.100
so I hauled it back for a bed base.

00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:40.740
We're missing the character here.

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:41.580
The meaning is different.

00:10:41.580 --> 00:10:42.660
It'll get us into trouble.

00:10:42.740 --> 00:10:43.660
Go get it back, now.

00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:45.500
We don't have time for that.

00:10:45.500 --> 00:10:46.380
What to do?

00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:48.100
Find something to cover this up first.

00:10:48.100 --> 00:10:48.980
- With what?
- Go.

00:10:48.980 --> 00:10:49.900
Go get a straw rain cape.

00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:51.820
Set up a scarecrow with it.

00:10:53.420 --> 00:10:54.260
Move, move.

00:10:57.740 --> 00:10:58.580
Quick.

00:10:59.580 --> 00:11:00.420
Give me the kid.

00:11:00.420 --> 00:11:01.300
What are you doing?

00:11:01.300 --> 00:11:02.140
Come on.

00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:02.980
Slow down.

00:11:02.980 --> 00:11:04.420
Up, up, up.

00:11:04.420 --> 00:11:05.260
Come here.

00:11:05.260 --> 00:11:06.700
Put it on the kid.

00:11:06.700 --> 00:11:07.540
Let her stand here.

00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:09.700
What are you doing?

00:11:09.700 --> 00:11:10.540
Stay out of it.

00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:13.900
The clothes are too new. They don't fit.

00:11:14.260 --> 00:11:15.340
Take it off.

00:11:15.340 --> 00:11:16.260
Come on. Over here.

00:11:16.380 --> 00:11:17.220
Come here.

00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:18.060
Come on.

00:11:19.060 --> 00:11:20.420
Come on. Shoes Bai.

00:11:20.420 --> 00:11:21.260
Shoes Bai,

00:11:21.260 --> 00:11:22.900
do you have some worn-out clothes

00:11:22.900 --> 00:11:23.740
for the kid?

00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:24.580
The more worn-out, the better.

00:11:24.860 --> 00:11:25.980
Worn-out?

00:11:27.220 --> 00:11:28.060
Hua Caixiang

00:11:28.060 --> 00:11:29.420
gave me a set of her clothes.

00:11:29.420 --> 00:11:30.260
They're worn out.

00:11:30.260 --> 00:11:31.140
Are they here?

00:11:31.140 --> 00:11:31.980
Yeah, yeah.

00:11:31.980 --> 00:11:32.940
I've washed them clean.

00:11:36.020 --> 00:11:37.140
Come on.

00:11:37.140 --> 00:11:37.980
That's great.

00:11:37.980 --> 00:11:38.820
Don't you like these clothes?

00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:39.900
Go change.

00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:41.660
I brought those shoes too.

00:11:41.660 --> 00:11:43.020
Okay. Where can she change?

00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:43.980
Here. Come on in.

00:11:43.980 --> 00:11:44.980
Quick. Go.

00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:45.820
Go put it on. Change.

00:11:48.260 --> 00:11:49.340
I'll help you with the top.

00:11:51.060 --> 00:11:52.460
What are you trying to do?

00:11:52.460 --> 00:11:53.340
Well...

00:11:53.340 --> 00:11:54.220
Stay out of it.

00:11:57.620 --> 00:11:58.580
Black greasepaint.

00:11:58.660 --> 00:11:59.500
What are you doing?

00:12:00.300 --> 00:12:01.540
I'll do some makeup.

00:12:02.660 --> 00:12:03.500
Done.

00:12:05.540 --> 00:12:06.380
All set.

00:12:06.380 --> 00:12:07.820
The collar, collar.

00:12:08.940 --> 00:12:09.820
Fix the collar.

00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:16.980
♪Gold and silver aren't enough♪

00:12:18.620 --> 00:12:21.220
♪Heaven above and earth below♪

00:12:22.780 --> 00:12:25.780
♪Kid, don't get cocky♪

00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:35.900
(Learn from Dazhai and Yang)

00:12:37.260 --> 00:12:38.580
What's standing back there?

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:42.980
It looks like a scarecrow.

00:12:43.660 --> 00:12:45.700
Why put up a scarecrow? Who did it?

00:12:47.740 --> 00:12:49.700
I don't know. It wasn't me.

00:12:51.420 --> 00:12:53.820
Maybe Director Glasses
tried something new.

00:12:58.300 --> 00:12:59.140
What's going on here?

00:13:01.060 --> 00:13:02.100
Who set this up?

00:13:34.100 --> 00:13:37.060
The red flag of progress

00:13:41.820 --> 00:13:44.220
waves in the wind.

00:13:56.300 --> 00:13:57.700
A little nervous.

00:14:08.060 --> 00:14:14.340
Clear waters and blue skies

00:14:17.180 --> 00:14:21.340
reflect the glowing clouds.

00:14:21.340 --> 00:14:24.740
For miles,

00:14:34.300 --> 00:14:36.140
the Luo River

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:41.220
rolls with surging waves.

00:14:41.220 --> 00:14:42.980
With a heart full of...

00:15:33.220 --> 00:15:35.380
Yi Qing'e had no idea
if her uncle's drumming

00:15:35.380 --> 00:15:36.740
was any good,

00:15:37.300 --> 00:15:40.500
but she could see he got more into it.

00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:43.060
She also saw Aunt Hua's face

00:15:43.060 --> 00:15:44.540
getting harder to watch.

00:15:44.740 --> 00:15:48.140
As Aunt Mi Lan sang
more and more powerfully,

00:15:48.340 --> 00:15:52.620
the crowd's cheers kept rising higher.

00:15:53.420 --> 00:15:54.900
It was her first time onstage,

00:15:54.900 --> 00:15:57.020
and as the scarecrow,

00:15:57.140 --> 00:16:00.900
she was the quietest role
in the whole play.

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:05.340
What are you doing?

00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:09.180
Hey. What did you do?

00:16:09.180 --> 00:16:10.020
She spat at you.

00:16:10.380 --> 00:16:11.660
Then why is her spit on your neck?

00:16:19.700 --> 00:16:21.020
Come on, come on.

00:16:21.420 --> 00:16:22.260
Hurry up. Come on.

00:16:22.900 --> 00:16:24.900
Your debut performance today was a hit.

00:16:27.420 --> 00:16:28.260
Come on.

00:16:28.260 --> 00:16:29.260
So, you're Hu Sanyuan?

00:16:30.140 --> 00:16:31.020
Yeah. What is it?

00:16:31.020 --> 00:16:31.860
Come with us.

00:16:32.180 --> 00:16:33.060
What's this about?

00:16:33.060 --> 00:16:34.060
You'll hear it at the station.

00:16:34.380 --> 00:16:35.220
Move.

00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:39.420
Go find your aunt.

00:16:39.740 --> 00:16:41.140
Help me put away the drumsticks.

00:16:42.540 --> 00:16:43.380
Let's go.

00:16:46.060 --> 00:16:47.460
He's taken away.

00:16:48.180 --> 00:16:49.300
What's up with Sanyuan?

00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:50.580
He's been possessed.

00:16:51.580 --> 00:16:52.540
By whom?

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:57.180
Congrats.

00:16:57.740 --> 00:16:58.660
You sang really well.

00:16:59.460 --> 00:17:01.580
I'm nowhere near you.

00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:03.500
It was mostly thanks
to Sanyuan's drumbeat

00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:05.020
and your guidance.

00:17:05.020 --> 00:17:06.220
What guidance did I give you?

00:17:06.900 --> 00:17:08.460
I finally found

00:17:08.460 --> 00:17:10.420
that feeling when the drumbeat
hits just right.

00:17:10.860 --> 00:17:12.020
When I first went on stage,

00:17:12.020 --> 00:17:13.500
I was really nervous.

00:17:13.500 --> 00:17:15.220
But Sanyuan's drumbeat made me

00:17:15.220 --> 00:17:16.580
stop being afraid of anything.

00:17:16.580 --> 00:17:17.980
Once I got on stage,

00:17:17.980 --> 00:17:19.020
I couldn't stop myself

00:17:19.020 --> 00:17:21.140
from singing out.

00:17:30.540 --> 00:17:31.660
How timid.

00:17:40.100 --> 00:17:41.460
(Chengguan Police Station)

00:17:41.460 --> 00:17:42.300
Hu Sanyuan,

00:17:43.100 --> 00:17:44.300
do you know why you're here?

00:17:45.260 --> 00:17:46.100
No, I don't.

00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:47.180
Think about it.

00:17:49.220 --> 00:17:50.780
If this is about the backdrop,

00:17:51.540 --> 00:17:53.500
I thought it was just a useless plank,

00:17:53.500 --> 00:17:55.100
so I took it home to use as a bed board.

00:17:55.100 --> 00:17:56.660
You can't blame Nail for that.

00:17:57.140 --> 00:17:58.140
I already fixed it up

00:17:58.140 --> 00:17:59.420
before the show.

00:17:59.420 --> 00:18:00.540
That's not what this is about.

00:18:01.420 --> 00:18:02.660
Then I really don't know.

00:18:03.420 --> 00:18:05.380
Something happened in the troupe.

00:18:06.100 --> 00:18:07.020
You know that, right?

00:18:10.260 --> 00:18:11.820
Everyone in the troupe knows by now.

00:18:12.940 --> 00:18:15.700
Someone sent Huang Zhengjing's wife
an anonymous letter.

00:18:16.940 --> 00:18:18.940
His wife came to the troupe

00:18:19.260 --> 00:18:20.580
and then took some pills.

00:18:23.820 --> 00:18:24.660
Go on.

00:18:28.180 --> 00:18:30.260
You think I wrote that anonymous letter?

00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:43.580
Sometimes, I don't like

00:18:44.820 --> 00:18:47.220
some of Huang Zhengjing's ways,

00:18:47.740 --> 00:18:49.060
but writing an anonymous letter

00:18:49.060 --> 00:18:50.380
isn't my style.

00:18:59.300 --> 00:19:00.340
Then what is your style?

00:19:09.580 --> 00:19:10.780
Is that your style?

00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:13.180
I've always been upfront.

00:19:13.180 --> 00:19:15.860
Tonight, when I saw you
playing the drums backstage,

00:19:15.860 --> 00:19:16.900
you were

00:19:17.180 --> 00:19:18.140
really wild.

00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:19.180
Is that your style?

00:19:19.180 --> 00:19:20.060
That was for the show.

00:19:20.060 --> 00:19:20.900
Hu Sanyuan,

00:19:20.900 --> 00:19:21.740
your Security Section

00:19:21.740 --> 00:19:23.500
has long had you on their key list.

00:19:24.500 --> 00:19:26.500
To them, I'm just a troublemaker.

00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:29.140
If anything stirs in the troupe,

00:19:29.140 --> 00:19:30.460
I'm the first one they think of.

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:33.460
Tell me. Why did you beat four drums?

00:19:36.700 --> 00:19:37.780
Shameless.

00:19:38.700 --> 00:19:40.700
She even got chills?

00:19:40.700 --> 00:19:41.580
She's not married.

00:19:41.580 --> 00:19:43.740
She's still green. What does she know?

00:19:46.860 --> 00:19:47.740
Your uncle is annoying.

00:19:48.580 --> 00:19:49.740
He reeks of that sleazy vibe,

00:19:49.740 --> 00:19:50.940
worse than a ram in heat.

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:54.900
Where's my uncle?

00:19:54.900 --> 00:19:56.060
The cops took him.

00:19:56.060 --> 00:19:57.140
For what?

00:19:57.140 --> 00:19:57.980
For acting indecently.

00:20:04.500 --> 00:20:05.740
Don't wear that outfit again.

00:20:06.340 --> 00:20:08.140
When you wear it, you seem off to me.

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:16.100
This is the ceremonial drum.

00:20:16.100 --> 00:20:18.580
It shows a bright, festive mood.

00:20:19.140 --> 00:20:20.900
The welcoming interlude

00:20:21.900 --> 00:20:23.700
for a top imperial scholar.

00:20:25.060 --> 00:20:27.580
The Baogu drum fits painted-face roles

00:20:27.580 --> 00:20:30.180
and hot-tempered Laosheng roles,

00:20:30.180 --> 00:20:33.580
with a strong, forceful tune and vocals.
Come on.

00:20:39.660 --> 00:20:42.700
The Gangu drum fits female vocals.

00:20:43.540 --> 00:20:45.860
It mostly brings out grace and clarity.

00:20:45.860 --> 00:20:47.700
Slow tempo, two-six meter.

00:20:54.660 --> 00:20:56.140
The Zhangu drum is like the name.

00:20:56.140 --> 00:20:57.980
It's for battle scenes
and martial plays.

00:21:03.060 --> 00:21:04.540
- Right.
- Then I'm heading out.

00:21:04.540 --> 00:21:05.380
We'll walk you out.

00:21:06.540 --> 00:21:08.900
Come find me at the troupe for a show.

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:09.780
Okay, okay.

00:21:09.780 --> 00:21:11.540
Your drumming is great. I'm telling you.

00:21:12.140 --> 00:21:13.260
Especially the Zhangu drum.

00:21:14.140 --> 00:21:15.220
It really hits hard.

00:21:15.220 --> 00:21:16.100
Yeah, yeah.

00:21:16.100 --> 00:21:16.940
Well.

00:21:17.380 --> 00:21:18.220
Okay, okay.

00:21:18.740 --> 00:21:19.740
- Okay.
- Take it slow.

00:21:22.660 --> 00:21:23.700
What brings you two here?

00:21:24.060 --> 00:21:24.900
What happened?

00:21:26.540 --> 00:21:27.540
It's about the anonymous letter.

00:21:27.820 --> 00:21:29.540
The Head of Security Section set me up.

00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:30.780
Serves you right.

00:21:30.780 --> 00:21:32.620
If he didn't, I would have.

00:21:32.820 --> 00:21:34.180
What are you talking about?

00:21:34.340 --> 00:21:35.180
Let's go.

00:21:35.180 --> 00:21:36.660
The police were nice to you.

00:21:36.660 --> 00:21:38.580
They walked you out and shook your hand.

00:21:38.700 --> 00:21:39.540
Who do you think I am?

00:21:39.540 --> 00:21:40.980
The Northwest Drum King, remember?

00:21:40.980 --> 00:21:42.100
Quit bragging already.

00:21:42.700 --> 00:21:43.540
Yi Qing'e,

00:21:43.900 --> 00:21:45.580
you did great as the scarecrow today.

00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:48.140
Your stage debut was a real success.

00:21:48.660 --> 00:21:49.820
Why haven't you changed yet?

00:21:49.820 --> 00:21:50.740
Little beggar.

00:21:51.860 --> 00:21:53.220
Was the letter from Mi Lan?

00:21:53.660 --> 00:21:54.660
No way.

00:21:54.660 --> 00:21:55.500
Why not?

00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:56.700
She benefits from this the most.

00:21:56.700 --> 00:21:58.340
She even took my spot as the lead.

00:21:58.820 --> 00:22:00.980
I don't think she's like that, okay?

00:22:01.940 --> 00:22:03.300
Then what kind of person is she?

00:22:03.300 --> 00:22:04.940
What are you doing? Why hit me?

00:22:04.940 --> 00:22:07.260
Who said to pound the drum to pieces?

00:22:07.260 --> 00:22:09.100
And then? You got more into it.

00:22:09.100 --> 00:22:10.500
She even got chills.

00:22:10.500 --> 00:22:11.420
I wasn't trying to play.

00:22:11.420 --> 00:22:13.060
The drumstick wanted to do it.

00:22:13.060 --> 00:22:13.900
What could I do?

00:22:15.380 --> 00:22:17.140
What's wrong with you?

00:22:17.140 --> 00:22:18.180
I didn't hit you.

00:22:18.180 --> 00:22:19.380
The drumstick wanted to do it.

00:22:21.020 --> 00:22:21.860
Stop right there.

00:22:22.740 --> 00:22:23.580
Hu Sanyuan!

00:22:30.740 --> 00:22:32.200
Honestly, your uncle and I...

00:22:33.820 --> 00:22:35.060
There's nothing going on at all.

00:22:36.580 --> 00:22:38.140
It's between a man and a woman.

00:22:39.180 --> 00:22:40.380
You won't get it.

00:22:41.700 --> 00:22:43.140
You'll understand when you're older.

00:22:44.700 --> 00:22:45.780
It's really wearing.

00:22:49.300 --> 00:22:50.300
Drop the act.

00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:52.700
I know you're still awake.

00:22:54.340 --> 00:22:55.780
You snore.

00:23:02.900 --> 00:23:04.100
Back then,

00:23:05.980 --> 00:23:07.180
I liked your uncle.

00:23:10.060 --> 00:23:11.700
Li Qing'e liked your uncle too.

00:23:13.100 --> 00:23:14.060
She could handle

00:23:15.180 --> 00:23:16.300
both civil and martial roles.

00:23:17.060 --> 00:23:18.900
In our trade, we call it all-round.

00:23:20.780 --> 00:23:22.540
In the troupe,

00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:24.580
we fought for the lead

00:23:25.260 --> 00:23:26.300
and your uncle.

00:23:28.060 --> 00:23:30.140
Your uncle is a fool.

00:23:31.780 --> 00:23:33.940
But somehow, he made

00:23:34.900 --> 00:23:37.020
the troupe's best two women

00:23:37.020 --> 00:23:38.620
jealous and compete over him.

00:23:41.820 --> 00:23:43.380
I lost to her on both counts.

00:23:45.500 --> 00:23:46.620
Once,

00:23:48.060 --> 00:23:49.660
Li Qing'e was in Dao Xian Cao.

00:23:52.380 --> 00:23:54.300
She was meant to climb three tables,

00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:55.740
pick the herb of immortality,

00:23:56.540 --> 00:23:58.540
and then flip down.

00:24:00.660 --> 00:24:03.340
But she learned some extra moves

00:24:05.100 --> 00:24:06.740
of bending back

00:24:07.300 --> 00:24:09.500
and grabbing the herb with her teeth.

00:24:11.580 --> 00:24:13.260
The audience went wild.

00:24:14.820 --> 00:24:15.820
The cheers

00:24:16.620 --> 00:24:18.660
nearly shook the stage apart.

00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:23.100
Your uncle got swept up too.

00:24:24.100 --> 00:24:25.620
He pounded the drum like crazy.

00:24:28.540 --> 00:24:29.500
Then,

00:24:30.580 --> 00:24:31.900
she lost focus for a second

00:24:33.780 --> 00:24:36.100
and fell from the three tables.

00:24:38.020 --> 00:24:39.220
She never got back up.

00:24:44.340 --> 00:24:45.620
By then,

00:24:47.340 --> 00:24:49.340
I'd already married out of spite.

00:24:55.900 --> 00:24:57.220
Your name is Qing'e.

00:24:58.660 --> 00:24:59.740
Good.

00:25:15.100 --> 00:25:16.140
Sanyuan.

00:25:17.300 --> 00:25:18.260
I'm coming in, okay?

00:25:21.540 --> 00:25:22.740
Why are you still up this late?

00:25:23.260 --> 00:25:24.420
I came to thank you.

00:25:24.820 --> 00:25:25.660
Why?

00:25:25.900 --> 00:25:27.940
Tonight's show worked thanks to you.

00:25:29.140 --> 00:25:30.540
No, you were the one who sang well.

00:25:31.060 --> 00:25:32.340
I put you in a tough spot, bro.

00:25:32.860 --> 00:25:33.980
What do you mean?

00:25:34.540 --> 00:25:37.260
Stop pretending. I get it.

00:25:39.260 --> 00:25:41.700
That drumstick was for the act, not you.

00:25:42.740 --> 00:25:43.620
Sanyuan,

00:25:43.620 --> 00:25:45.300
when I went to perform
in the provincial capital,

00:25:45.300 --> 00:25:47.180
I bought a towel
at the department store.

00:25:47.180 --> 00:25:48.900
I couldn't bear to use it.

00:25:48.900 --> 00:25:50.180
Now, I'm giving it to you

00:25:50.180 --> 00:25:51.620
to show how grateful I am.

00:25:51.620 --> 00:25:52.500
What are you doing?

00:25:53.100 --> 00:25:54.300
We're in the same troupe.

00:25:54.300 --> 00:25:55.140
Take it back.

00:25:55.140 --> 00:25:56.060
I wouldn't dare.

00:25:56.060 --> 00:25:57.380
Why were the police after you?

00:25:58.180 --> 00:25:59.060
About the anonymous letter.

00:26:00.060 --> 00:26:01.380
Then why did they single you out?

00:26:02.660 --> 00:26:04.220
The Head of Security Section

00:26:04.220 --> 00:26:05.420
thought I wrote it.

00:26:05.420 --> 00:26:06.620
He's such a jerk.

00:26:10.900 --> 00:26:11.740
What are you doing?

00:26:15.500 --> 00:26:16.340
I wouldn't dare.

00:26:16.940 --> 00:26:17.780
I wouldn't.

00:26:18.300 --> 00:26:19.740
A towel is enough.

00:26:21.380 --> 00:26:22.900
I had someone write that letter.

00:26:26.620 --> 00:26:27.460
This...

00:26:27.660 --> 00:26:29.380
He kept talking to me all day long,

00:26:29.380 --> 00:26:30.260
dropping hints.

00:26:30.260 --> 00:26:31.260
Sometimes, he'd get handsy.

00:26:31.260 --> 00:26:32.900
I really couldn't take it anymore.

00:26:32.900 --> 00:26:35.300
I didn't mean to set up Caixiang.

00:26:35.300 --> 00:26:36.420
I just wanted his wife

00:26:36.420 --> 00:26:38.020
to watch him in the troupe.

00:26:38.020 --> 00:26:39.780
Right. So, you got what you wanted.

00:26:40.300 --> 00:26:42.060
He had a thing for Caixiang too.

00:26:42.060 --> 00:26:43.220
But Caixiang was

00:26:43.220 --> 00:26:44.300
more seasoned than I was.

00:26:44.300 --> 00:26:45.700
And you were protecting her in secret.

00:26:46.220 --> 00:26:48.060
No one was looking out for me.

00:26:48.060 --> 00:26:49.660
So, I had no choice
but to do it this way

00:26:49.660 --> 00:26:50.820
to protect myself.

00:26:51.060 --> 00:26:52.980
Why are you telling me this?

00:26:53.820 --> 00:26:55.540
What do you expect me to do?

00:26:56.180 --> 00:26:57.940
Keep this buried deep inside.

00:26:57.940 --> 00:26:59.180
Don't tell anyone.

00:26:59.260 --> 00:27:00.900
I wouldn't dare tell anyone else.

00:27:00.900 --> 00:27:02.100
I didn't hear a thing either.

00:27:02.100 --> 00:27:03.540
You didn't tell me anything.

00:27:04.300 --> 00:27:05.140
Got it?

00:27:06.180 --> 00:27:07.020
Okay.

00:27:11.660 --> 00:27:12.500
Sanyuan,

00:27:12.780 --> 00:27:14.740
about your niece's troupe exam,

00:27:15.260 --> 00:27:16.100
I know.

00:27:40.620 --> 00:27:42.420
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

00:27:42.420 --> 00:27:43.620
Forget everyone else.

00:27:44.620 --> 00:27:46.260
Can we even accept this ourselves?

00:27:47.220 --> 00:27:49.260
The troupe is taking trainees,

00:27:49.740 --> 00:27:51.820
not picking acts for a circus.

00:27:52.220 --> 00:27:53.500
You brought in someone this slow.

00:27:53.500 --> 00:27:54.740
He can't even talk to me.

00:27:55.060 --> 00:27:56.780
How is he fit to perform in opera?

00:27:57.420 --> 00:27:58.380
Take this one back now.

00:27:58.380 --> 00:27:59.380
Forget it.

00:27:59.380 --> 00:28:01.260
Stop embarrassing yourself here.

00:28:04.340 --> 00:28:05.380
Yinwa,

00:28:05.700 --> 00:28:08.220
people aim higher, as water flows down.

00:28:08.220 --> 00:28:10.060
We've got to learn to move up.

00:28:11.180 --> 00:28:12.380
After all,

00:28:12.380 --> 00:28:15.100
you're my wife,

00:28:15.220 --> 00:28:17.540
not some production team leader's wife,

00:28:18.300 --> 00:28:19.140
right?

00:28:19.660 --> 00:28:21.780
You need to see the big picture.

00:28:21.780 --> 00:28:23.180
You should let it go.

00:28:23.180 --> 00:28:25.820
That suits your status.

00:28:25.820 --> 00:28:27.540
Cut the sweet talk.

00:28:27.740 --> 00:28:29.140
Get me some DDVP insecticide.

00:28:29.140 --> 00:28:30.660
I promise I'll improve even faster.

00:28:30.940 --> 00:28:32.820
Why won't this get through to you?

00:28:35.500 --> 00:28:36.580
When did you come?

00:28:37.500 --> 00:28:38.380
What's up?

00:28:38.380 --> 00:28:40.420
Director Huang,
I heard your wife came back.

00:28:40.900 --> 00:28:42.060
Is she okay?

00:28:42.900 --> 00:28:44.740
She's fine. What do you want?

00:28:44.740 --> 00:28:46.060
Then I'm relieved.

00:28:46.820 --> 00:28:48.220
She really needs to be talked to.

00:28:49.180 --> 00:28:51.060
She mustn't act on impulse.

00:28:51.860 --> 00:28:54.260
When trouble comes,
she shouldn't avoid it

00:28:54.260 --> 00:28:55.500
and deal with herself.

00:28:55.500 --> 00:28:57.060
Mind your own business.

00:28:57.620 --> 00:28:58.620
What do you need?

00:28:59.100 --> 00:28:59.940
Here's the thing.

00:29:00.340 --> 00:29:01.740
After the show ended yesterday,

00:29:01.740 --> 00:29:03.220
the police called me in.

00:29:03.540 --> 00:29:04.860
It was about the anonymous letter.

00:29:05.660 --> 00:29:06.860
I had to report it to you.

00:29:07.220 --> 00:29:09.060
Guess what conclusion they reached.

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:11.340
They said that from the way I play,

00:29:11.340 --> 00:29:13.020
they could see my integrity.

00:29:13.740 --> 00:29:16.660
That I'm someone who acts openly.

00:29:16.660 --> 00:29:17.500
Alright, enough.

00:29:17.500 --> 00:29:18.780
I know what kind of man you are.

00:29:19.420 --> 00:29:20.860
Why did you come today?

00:29:20.860 --> 00:29:21.700
Well.

00:29:21.900 --> 00:29:23.660
This is my niece.

00:29:25.060 --> 00:29:27.300
My sister's family is struggling.

00:29:27.780 --> 00:29:29.700
They can barely feed the child.

00:29:29.700 --> 00:29:30.540
They had no choice.

00:29:30.780 --> 00:29:32.820
So, I brought her to the troupe.

00:29:32.820 --> 00:29:34.380
Maybe she can make a living here.

00:29:34.980 --> 00:29:36.140
I should report it to you too.

00:29:37.020 --> 00:29:38.020
Greet Uncle Huang.

00:29:38.900 --> 00:29:40.060
No need.

00:29:40.580 --> 00:29:42.500
They said this kid is mute.

00:29:43.020 --> 00:29:44.940
Who said that? I'll shut them up.

00:29:45.340 --> 00:29:46.340
How could she be mute?

00:29:46.980 --> 00:29:48.620
Just wait. She'll speak soon.

00:29:50.620 --> 00:29:51.620
Study hard for the exam.

00:29:51.620 --> 00:29:53.340
You have to get in, okay?

00:29:54.980 --> 00:29:55.980
Uncle Huang is kind.

00:29:55.980 --> 00:29:58.260
Look, he's got two rooms at home.

00:29:58.740 --> 00:29:59.780
Even if you don't get in,

00:29:59.780 --> 00:30:01.820
you won't go hungry here.

00:30:01.820 --> 00:30:02.660
Got it?

00:30:03.260 --> 00:30:04.780
But you need to be sensible.

00:30:04.780 --> 00:30:06.540
You have to work hard yourself.

00:30:06.540 --> 00:30:08.220
Don't make trouble for Uncle Huang.

00:30:08.540 --> 00:30:09.380
Do you hear me?

00:30:10.380 --> 00:30:13.060
Your uncle plays the drums,

00:30:13.060 --> 00:30:14.260
but he's better at extortion.

00:30:15.060 --> 00:30:16.340
As for me,

00:30:16.340 --> 00:30:18.100
my job is fixing problems.

00:30:18.700 --> 00:30:20.020
So, I'm not afraid of trouble.

00:30:20.580 --> 00:30:21.420
Got it?

00:30:22.060 --> 00:30:23.620
The kid seems really sensible.

00:30:24.140 --> 00:30:25.340
Better than some grown-ups.

00:30:43.980 --> 00:30:44.900
What brings you here?

00:30:55.500 --> 00:30:56.700
This is your niece, right?

00:30:57.260 --> 00:30:58.100
How did you know?

00:30:58.900 --> 00:31:00.540
Everyone in the troupe knows her.

00:31:01.140 --> 00:31:03.700
She caught snakes and played scarecrow.

00:31:04.420 --> 00:31:05.260
That was you, right?

00:31:06.180 --> 00:31:07.820
Do you know why she played scarecrow?

00:31:08.860 --> 00:31:10.220
Nail told me.

00:31:10.740 --> 00:31:12.780
The curtain was about to open.

00:31:12.780 --> 00:31:13.740
Too urgent to tell you.

00:31:14.100 --> 00:31:15.740
Huang Zhengjing even asked me

00:31:15.740 --> 00:31:17.940
why there was a scarecrow onstage.

00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:19.340
What did you say?

00:31:21.180 --> 00:31:23.220
I said it was my little experiment

00:31:23.220 --> 00:31:24.620
to enrich the stage.

00:31:25.940 --> 00:31:26.780
Did he buy it?

00:31:29.020 --> 00:31:30.980
He said the experiment worked.

00:31:30.980 --> 00:31:33.140
We should promote this method later.

00:31:33.900 --> 00:31:34.740
I owe you one.

00:31:35.380 --> 00:31:36.660
How do you plan to repay me?

00:31:38.100 --> 00:31:38.940
By owing you one more.

00:31:39.700 --> 00:31:40.540
I'll pay them back together.

00:31:42.860 --> 00:31:43.700
What do you mean?

00:31:45.220 --> 00:31:46.260
She wants to be a trainee.

00:31:51.140 --> 00:31:52.300
Everyone is saying

00:31:52.300 --> 00:31:55.060
you and Hua Caixiang
are teaching a mute opera.

00:31:57.540 --> 00:31:58.660
Nothing good ever comes

00:31:58.660 --> 00:32:00.060
from He Dachui.

00:32:00.180 --> 00:32:01.180
How is she mute?

00:32:01.300 --> 00:32:02.140
She can talk.

00:32:03.500 --> 00:32:04.340
She can?

00:32:05.260 --> 00:32:06.580
Have her sing for me.

00:32:08.500 --> 00:32:09.340
She can't.

00:32:10.180 --> 00:32:11.020
Then let her dance.

00:32:11.220 --> 00:32:12.060
She can't.

00:32:12.780 --> 00:32:14.780
She can't sing or dance,

00:32:14.780 --> 00:32:16.220
so why have her join the troupe?

00:32:17.500 --> 00:32:19.580
We want trainees, not actresses.

00:32:20.060 --> 00:32:21.540
She can learn after she gets in.

00:32:23.380 --> 00:32:25.140
At first, that almost sounds right.

00:32:26.220 --> 00:32:27.380
I'm not praising you.

00:32:27.940 --> 00:32:29.260
Quit talking nonsense here.

00:32:29.260 --> 00:32:30.380
I'm not getting involved in this.

00:32:33.780 --> 00:32:35.780
Her first time onstage

00:32:35.780 --> 00:32:38.380
went to your scarecrow act.

00:32:38.380 --> 00:32:39.380
You can't ignore that.

00:32:40.820 --> 00:32:42.500
Why are you being so unreasonable?

00:32:43.340 --> 00:32:45.180
Which part of what I said was wrong?

00:32:48.500 --> 00:32:50.060
Sure, I am one of the examiners.

00:32:50.580 --> 00:32:52.100
But I am not the only examiner.

00:32:52.100 --> 00:32:53.420
But you are the most loyal one.

00:32:54.380 --> 00:32:55.780
And the one who matters most.

00:32:57.980 --> 00:32:59.780
Her future is in your hands.

00:33:00.260 --> 00:33:01.740
Do not flatter me like that.

00:33:01.740 --> 00:33:02.780
I can't take that.

00:33:10.620 --> 00:33:11.900
The exam is tomorrow.

00:33:12.300 --> 00:33:13.340
Let Hua Caixiang

00:33:13.340 --> 00:33:15.500
teach her a song.

00:33:15.900 --> 00:33:16.860
She can't play scarecrow

00:33:16.860 --> 00:33:17.980
in the exam, right?

00:33:18.900 --> 00:33:20.060
Caixiang tried,

00:33:20.740 --> 00:33:21.660
but she wouldn't sing.

00:33:22.020 --> 00:33:23.980
Then what can I do?

00:33:25.380 --> 00:33:26.540
Just get out of here.

00:33:26.540 --> 00:33:28.220
Leave now, or I'll lose my temper.

00:33:28.860 --> 00:33:29.780
If she gets in,

00:33:29.780 --> 00:33:30.900
you can say whatever you want.

00:33:34.140 --> 00:33:35.580
I'm going to see Huang Zhengjing now.

00:33:35.580 --> 00:33:36.860
You can be the examiner.

00:33:36.860 --> 00:33:37.700
I'm done with this.

00:33:38.300 --> 00:33:39.140
Let's go.

00:33:39.140 --> 00:33:39.980
I'll go with you.

00:33:40.580 --> 00:33:41.420
Come on, let's go.

00:33:41.740 --> 00:33:42.580
Let go.

00:33:42.780 --> 00:33:43.620
Look here.

00:33:44.180 --> 00:33:45.020
Keep your eyes on him.

00:33:45.500 --> 00:33:46.780
This will keep you fed for life.

00:33:48.260 --> 00:33:49.100
You're this one.

00:33:54.340 --> 00:33:55.740
This place

00:33:55.740 --> 00:33:58.380
is where I practice.

00:33:59.020 --> 00:34:00.740
I trained here as a kid.

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:03.180
Back then, this tree wasn't so big.

00:34:04.860 --> 00:34:06.020
This is a lucky tree.

00:34:07.180 --> 00:34:08.900
It helped make Aunt Hua who she is,

00:34:08.900 --> 00:34:10.260
so it can help you too.

00:34:11.100 --> 00:34:11.940
Alright.

00:34:12.220 --> 00:34:13.380
Train with Aunt Hua.

00:34:14.620 --> 00:34:16.340
Come on,
let's do vocal projection practice.

00:34:16.340 --> 00:34:17.820
Face this way. It's nice and open.

00:34:20.020 --> 00:34:21.860
I'll call one line; you repeat it.

00:34:25.020 --> 00:34:27.980
Hu Sanyuan.

00:34:29.340 --> 00:34:30.180
I'm here.

00:34:31.420 --> 00:34:32.980
Don't teach her nonsense.

00:34:32.980 --> 00:34:34.300
This is part of the practice.

00:34:34.300 --> 00:34:36.660
Voice-opening exercises. Basic stuff.

00:34:36.660 --> 00:34:37.780
Alright, go on, call out.

00:34:38.700 --> 00:34:39.980
Call out. Repeat after Aunt Hua.

00:34:41.980 --> 00:34:45.140
Hu Sanyuan.

00:34:45.380 --> 00:34:48.300
Hu Sanyuan.

00:34:50.340 --> 00:34:53.380
Jerk.

00:34:54.220 --> 00:34:55.580
Part of the practice?

00:34:55.580 --> 00:34:59.540
Jerk.

00:35:00.660 --> 00:35:01.500
Shout it.

00:35:03.940 --> 00:35:04.780
What are you looking at?

00:35:05.220 --> 00:35:06.660
Repeat after Aunt Hua.

00:35:08.940 --> 00:35:09.780
Shout it.

00:35:11.100 --> 00:35:13.780
Jerk.

00:35:14.340 --> 00:35:16.140
She's got a really clear voice.

00:35:16.140 --> 00:35:16.980
See?

00:35:17.900 --> 00:35:19.980
Did she make
a stunning first impression?

00:35:20.540 --> 00:35:22.740
Come on, let's sing.

00:35:23.660 --> 00:35:25.900
What are you staring at?
Look at your aunt.

00:35:27.620 --> 00:35:29.220
Repeat after me.

00:35:29.220 --> 00:35:30.820
Isn't Aunt Hua as cute as the sheep?

00:35:32.980 --> 00:35:33.820
Come on.

00:35:33.900 --> 00:35:36.060
You can rhyme.

00:35:36.340 --> 00:35:38.060
I can rhyme.

00:35:38.060 --> 00:35:42.100
You have so much strength.

00:35:42.580 --> 00:35:45.460
Let's see what your wife says.

00:35:45.460 --> 00:35:47.100
Work really makes people happy.

00:35:48.060 --> 00:35:48.900
We're having fun.

00:35:49.700 --> 00:35:51.620
Look how pleased you are.

00:35:52.020 --> 00:35:52.860
Dad.

00:35:53.220 --> 00:35:54.060
What?

00:35:54.460 --> 00:35:55.380
I need to talk to you.

00:35:55.860 --> 00:35:56.700
What's wrong?

00:35:56.700 --> 00:35:57.540
Come out and talk.

00:35:58.060 --> 00:35:59.460
That little brat surely has nerve.

00:35:59.460 --> 00:36:00.300
Go on.

00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:02.060
What needs to be said outside?

00:36:03.620 --> 00:36:04.460
What's wrong?

00:36:04.660 --> 00:36:05.500
Look at me.

00:36:09.900 --> 00:36:10.740
Wait, there's more.

00:36:15.060 --> 00:36:15.900
So, how am I?

00:36:17.220 --> 00:36:18.060
How am I?

00:36:18.820 --> 00:36:19.660
Go tend the fire.

00:36:20.100 --> 00:36:22.300
Song Guangzu, I'm begging you.

00:36:22.300 --> 00:36:23.620
It's the last day. Help me...

00:36:25.260 --> 00:36:26.460
Go tend the fire!

00:36:47.980 --> 00:36:48.820
I'm hungry.

00:37:11.700 --> 00:37:13.620
If only we could trade places.

00:37:15.300 --> 00:37:16.620
A person's fate is set by heaven.

00:37:18.140 --> 00:37:18.980
You can't change it.

00:37:19.140 --> 00:37:26.940
(Boiling Water Time)

00:37:26.940 --> 00:37:27.780
Brat,

00:37:28.420 --> 00:37:30.700
I heard you're trying
for the troupe too.

00:37:35.260 --> 00:37:37.580
Why don't you take
a good look at yourself?

00:37:37.580 --> 00:37:38.580
Are you good enough?

00:37:39.540 --> 00:37:42.300
What were you thinking?

00:37:42.300 --> 00:37:44.180
If you get in, even pigs can get in.

00:37:44.180 --> 00:37:45.020
Got that?

00:37:46.180 --> 00:37:47.300
Who is he?

00:37:47.860 --> 00:37:49.140
A fool.

00:37:49.660 --> 00:37:51.380
His dad is the Head of Security Section.

00:37:52.300 --> 00:37:54.020
He's just throwing his weight around,

00:37:54.020 --> 00:37:55.700
picking on outsiders like us.

00:38:01.220 --> 00:38:02.060
What are you looking at?

00:38:06.500 --> 00:38:08.500
Oh, you're getting bold now?

00:38:08.500 --> 00:38:10.620
Go on, keep staring at me.

00:38:11.860 --> 00:38:12.700
Go on.

00:38:12.700 --> 00:38:13.980
I'll deal with you.

00:38:14.220 --> 00:38:15.260
Keep staring. Come on.

00:38:18.260 --> 00:38:19.860
You're asking for it.

00:38:20.500 --> 00:38:22.260
Watch yourself from now on.

00:38:26.180 --> 00:38:27.700
I'll grow up.

00:38:29.180 --> 00:38:30.900
When I see you, I'll hit you

00:38:31.460 --> 00:38:33.060
till you beg me for mercy.

00:38:33.940 --> 00:38:36.180
Attention, attention!

00:38:36.620 --> 00:38:38.580
To launch
the Patriotic Public Health Campaign

00:38:38.580 --> 00:38:40.540
and wipe out the Four Pests,

00:38:41.060 --> 00:38:44.620
the whole county will use
the BHC powder at 6 p.m.

00:38:45.260 --> 00:38:46.420
Let's wipe out pests,

00:38:46.420 --> 00:38:47.700
clean up our homes,

00:38:47.980 --> 00:38:49.260
and reduce disease.

00:38:49.260 --> 00:38:51.540
We hope everyone joins in.

00:38:52.260 --> 00:38:53.940
Please close your doors and windows.

00:38:54.340 --> 00:38:55.300
Is there any on your face?

00:38:56.140 --> 00:38:57.740
Not on your eyes or mouth?

00:38:58.100 --> 00:39:00.020
Take her outside for a lap.

00:39:00.020 --> 00:39:00.860
It needs airing out.

00:39:01.620 --> 00:39:03.100
I should air out my room too.

00:39:03.740 --> 00:39:04.780
Go ahead. We're leaving.

00:39:07.740 --> 00:39:08.980
The whole yard is full of smoke.

00:39:13.540 --> 00:39:14.380
Hurry up.

00:39:14.380 --> 00:39:15.820
Kid, go stroll on the street.

00:39:21.460 --> 00:39:22.340
Go, go.

00:39:22.340 --> 00:39:23.700
- It's choking me.
- Too much smoke.

00:39:23.700 --> 00:39:24.740
Move, hurry.

00:39:25.500 --> 00:39:26.340
Go, go.

00:39:30.700 --> 00:39:31.540
Come on.

00:39:38.140 --> 00:39:39.100
Come on, come on.

00:39:45.500 --> 00:39:46.820
He Dachui calls

00:39:46.820 --> 00:39:47.660
Why are you here?

00:39:47.660 --> 00:39:50.180
the little yellow dog Hu Siyuan.

00:39:50.700 --> 00:39:53.820
Hu Sanyuan calls it He Erchui.

00:39:54.780 --> 00:39:56.740
We have no idea if the dog minds,

00:39:57.100 --> 00:39:58.860
but those two have fought for years.

00:39:59.140 --> 00:40:01.100
There's never a quiet moment.

00:40:24.820 --> 00:40:25.660
Move, move.

00:40:25.660 --> 00:40:26.500
Hurry up.

00:40:26.500 --> 00:40:27.620
Hurry, hurry, get out.

00:40:31.500 --> 00:40:32.900
Move, move, hurry up.

00:40:40.060 --> 00:40:41.700
Why climb out of the window?

00:40:42.140 --> 00:40:42.980
You did it?

00:40:43.500 --> 00:40:45.340
It's to wipe out the Four Pests.

00:40:45.340 --> 00:40:46.900
How did it smoke you out?

00:40:46.900 --> 00:40:48.580
You idiot. What do you want?

00:40:48.660 --> 00:40:49.700
You fool.

00:40:51.380 --> 00:40:52.940
This is a sacred rehearsal hall.

00:40:53.340 --> 00:40:54.500
And you're doing that in here?

00:40:55.340 --> 00:40:56.820
You're asking for trouble.

00:40:58.060 --> 00:40:59.300
I'll skin you alive.

00:40:59.500 --> 00:41:01.300
You've got some nerve, don't you?

00:41:02.940 --> 00:41:04.820
Her man's from the slaughterhouse.

00:41:05.340 --> 00:41:07.100
Watch out, or he'll butcher you.

00:41:07.460 --> 00:41:08.900
If word gets out about this,

00:41:09.100 --> 00:41:10.140
you're done for.

00:41:10.340 --> 00:41:11.540
I'm done for?

00:41:14.500 --> 00:41:15.660
I'm done for, huh?

00:41:17.500 --> 00:41:20.580
Whether this gets out depends on you.

00:41:20.580 --> 00:41:21.740
What do you want?

00:41:22.820 --> 00:41:23.740
Here's the situation.

00:41:24.700 --> 00:41:26.180
The troupe is recruiting trainees.

00:41:26.620 --> 00:41:29.420
I went back to my hometown and bragged.

00:41:29.940 --> 00:41:31.820
Then I brought my niece to audition.

00:41:32.620 --> 00:41:33.940
I was supposed to be the examiner.

00:41:34.260 --> 00:41:35.100
But when I got back,

00:41:35.100 --> 00:41:36.180
it ended up being you.

00:41:36.860 --> 00:41:39.340
That really caught me off guard.

00:41:40.420 --> 00:41:42.020
About my niece,

00:41:42.980 --> 00:41:44.140
you've got to help me out.

00:41:45.340 --> 00:41:46.860
The troupe doesn't allow favors.

00:41:46.860 --> 00:41:47.900
Alright, alright.

00:41:48.660 --> 00:41:49.500
No favors, huh?

00:41:49.500 --> 00:41:50.860
So, you went behind the mirror?

00:41:51.140 --> 00:41:51.980
Right.

00:41:52.660 --> 00:41:53.500
Just wait here.

00:41:54.380 --> 00:41:55.220
Just wait.

00:41:55.460 --> 00:41:56.300
Wait.

00:41:56.300 --> 00:41:58.620
Sometimes, I can keep a tight lid.

00:41:58.620 --> 00:42:00.020
Other times, I spill everything.

00:42:00.020 --> 00:42:01.140
You're impossible.

00:42:01.220 --> 00:42:02.180
Then it's settled, okay?

00:42:09.260 --> 00:42:13.620
(Ningzhou Cinema)

00:42:13.620 --> 00:42:17.660
♪The red star warms our hearts♪

00:42:18.140 --> 00:42:22.300
♪The red star is the heart
of the workers and peasants♪

00:42:22.460 --> 00:42:26.860
♪The Party's glory shines
for generations♪

00:42:26.940 --> 00:42:31.100
♪The red star is the heart
of the workers and peasants♪

00:42:31.100 --> 00:42:35.300
♪The Party's glory shines
for generations♪

00:42:35.300 --> 00:42:36.860
Hu Sanyuan from the County Troupe,

00:42:36.860 --> 00:42:37.940
someone's here for you.

00:42:38.660 --> 00:42:40.500
Hu Sanyuan from the County Troupe,

00:42:40.500 --> 00:42:41.580
someone's here for you.

00:42:42.180 --> 00:42:43.020
Who's here for you?

00:42:45.220 --> 00:42:46.100
They even came here?

00:42:51.700 --> 00:42:52.540
Who's looking for me?

00:42:54.420 --> 00:42:55.340
Who wants Hu Sanyuan?

00:43:01.220 --> 00:43:02.260
Hu Sanyuan.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:09.240
(County Troupe New Trainee Audition Room)

00:43:09.240 --> 00:43:12.400
We're taking in 30 trainees in total.

00:43:12.400 --> 00:43:14.520
Strike a snake at its vital spot.

00:43:14.520 --> 00:43:16.040
Please don't make this hard for me.

00:43:16.040 --> 00:43:18.360
At this tryout, there are five examiners.

00:43:18.360 --> 00:43:21.840
♪The red star is twinkling♪

00:43:21.840 --> 00:43:22.680
Sing.

00:43:22.800 --> 00:43:24.080
Where did my uncle go?

00:43:24.080 --> 00:43:25.720
Why are you giving up so easily?

00:43:25.720 --> 00:43:26.960
I don't want to sing.

00:43:27.120 --> 00:43:28.240
I want to go home.

00:43:28.240 --> 00:43:29.080
Yi Qing'e.

00:43:29.160 --> 00:43:30.200
Now, perform the piece

00:43:30.200 --> 00:43:31.240
you prepared.

00:43:31.360 --> 00:43:32.240
Sing.

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:41.620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:47.930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.560
♪We met and brushed past♪

00:43:55.120 --> 00:44:02.420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:20.540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:27.710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

00:44:28.830 --> 00:44:32.890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:39.610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:44.970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:51.640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:57.500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:03.350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:09.050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:15.510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:21.170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

00:45:22.120 --> 00:45:27.930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

00:45:27.930 --> 00:45:33.350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:39.410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:51.220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

00:45:52.020 --> 00:46:01.050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪